  "bodyHtml": "<head>\n<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\">\n<style type=\"text/css\" style=\"display:none;\"> P {margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;} </style>\n</head>\n<body dir=\"ltr\">\n<div class=\"elementToProof\" style=\"font-family: Aptos, Aptos_EmbeddedFont, Aptos_MSFontService, Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">\nHello</div>\n<div class=\"elementToProof\" style=\"font-family: Aptos, Aptos_EmbeddedFont, Aptos_MSFontService, Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">\n<br>\n</div>\n<div class=\"elementToProof\" style=\"font-family: Aptos, Aptos_EmbeddedFont, Aptos_MSFontService, Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">\nThank you for the insightful response! We appreciate your transparency, feedback and addressing of some of the issues we've pointed out.</div>\n<div class=\"elementToProof\" style=\"font-family: Aptos, Aptos_EmbeddedFont, Aptos_MSFontService, Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">\n<br>\n</div>\n<div class=\"elementToProof\" style=\"font-family: Aptos, Aptos_EmbeddedFont, Aptos_MSFontService, Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">\n<span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Regarding no CAPTCHA in email-change form – please consider, that if the attacker were to manually obtain an authorization token at login once, they later could run a potentially\n<b>unlimited</b>&nbsp;number of queries with that token.</span></div>\n<div class=\"elementToProof\" style=\"font-family: Aptos, Aptos_EmbeddedFont, Aptos_MSFontService, Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">\n<br>\n</div>\n<div class=\"elementToProof\" style=\"font-family: Aptos, Aptos_EmbeddedFont, Aptos_MSFontService, Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">\nRegarding the UX considerations you have mentioned, we understand the user-facing different behaviour depending on account existence to be considered\n<b>processing</b>&nbsp;of <b>personal data</b>&nbsp;under <b>EU's GDPR regulation </b>(see <a href=\"https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:32016R0679#art_4\" id=\"LPlnk718551\" class=\"OWAAutoLink\" title=\"https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:32016R0679#art_4\">\nArticle 4 – Definitions</a>). We are not aware of any <b>lawful basis</b>&nbsp;for doing so (see\n<a href=\"https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:32016R0679#art_6\" id=\"LPlnk271471\" class=\"OWAAutoLink\" title=\"https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:32016R0679#art_6\">\nArticle 6 – Lawfulness of processing</a>).</div>\n<div class=\"elementToProof\" style=\"font-family: Aptos, Aptos_EmbeddedFont, Aptos_MSFontService, Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">\n<br>\n</div>\n<div class=\"elementToProof\" style=\"font-family: Aptos, Aptos_EmbeddedFont, Aptos_MSFontService, Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">\nMoreover, we think <b>good UX is achievable&nbsp;in a compliant way</b>&nbsp;for registration:</div>\n<ol start=\"1\" data-editing-info=\"{&quot;applyListStyleFromLevel&quot;:false,&quot;orderedStyleType&quot;:1}\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<li style=\"font-family: Aptos, Aptos_EmbeddedFont, Aptos_MSFontService, Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">\n<div class=\"elementToProof\">First ask for email, then show \"further instructions have been sent\"</div>\n</li><li style=\"font-family: Aptos, Aptos_EmbeddedFont, Aptos_MSFontService, Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">\n<div class=\"elementToProof\">Send situation-dependent instructions</div>\n</li><ol start=\"1\" data-editing-info=\"{&quot;applyListStyleFromLevel&quot;:true}\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; list-style-type: lower-alpha;\">\n<li style=\"font-family: Aptos, Aptos_EmbeddedFont, Aptos_MSFontService, Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">\n<div class=\"elementToProof\">If email&nbsp;already exists: explain the situation and offer a password reset link instead.</div>\n</li><li style=\"font-family: Aptos, Aptos_EmbeddedFont, Aptos_MSFontService, Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">\n<div class=\"elementToProof\">If email does not exist: offer an email confirmation link to continue the sign-up process.</div>\n</li></ol>\n</ol>\n<div class=\"elementToProof\" style=\"font-family: Aptos, Aptos_EmbeddedFont, Aptos_MSFontService, Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">\nSimilar holds for email-change requests. This approach to UX is arguably even better, as the system would immediately send password recovery instructions without requiring the user to take multiple steps.</div>\n<div class=\"elementToProof\" style=\"font-family: Aptos, Aptos_EmbeddedFont, Aptos_MSFontService, Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">\n<br>\n</div>\n<div class=\"elementToProof\" style=\"font-family: Aptos, Aptos_EmbeddedFont, Aptos_MSFontService, Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">\nIn general, the goal of such approach is to authorize email owner before revealing any specific details. Similarly, personal codes could be authorized via eID (ID-card, Mobile-ID or Smart ID) means.</div>\n<div class=\"elementToProof\" style=\"font-family: Aptos, Aptos_EmbeddedFont, Aptos_MSFontService, Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">\n<br>\nWe are very interested in your further interpretation and assessment regarding the above. To save us time following up via formal means (rights specified in\n<a href=\"https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:32016R0679#art_15\" id=\"OWAded34142-023c-f274-8db5-bc2a02803935\" class=\"OWAAutoLink elementToProof\" style=\"margin: 0px; text-align: left;\">\nGDPR Articles 15-21</a>&nbsp;etc), perhaps you wish to also comment&nbsp;on our line of thinking:</div>\n<ul data-editing-info=\"{&quot;applyListStyleFromLevel&quot;:false,&quot;unorderedStyleType&quot;:2}\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;\">\n<li style=\"font-family: Aptos, Aptos_EmbeddedFont, Aptos_MSFontService, Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); list-style-type: &quot;- &quot;;\">\n<div class=\"elementToProof\">Whether or not an account exists is <b>personal data</b>&nbsp;(<a href=\"https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:32016R0679#art_4\" id=\"LPlnk756579\" class=\"OWAAutoLink\" title=\"https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:32016R0679#art_4\">Article\n 4(1)</a>)</div>\n</li><li style=\"font-family: Aptos, Aptos_EmbeddedFont, Aptos_MSFontService, Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); list-style-type: &quot;- &quot;;\">\n<div class=\"elementToProof\">Acknowledging account existence is <b>processing</b>&nbsp;of personal data&nbsp;(<a href=\"https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:32016R0679#art_4\" id=\"OWA07726dd7-1340-b7cf-c9a5-5ed846b3d184\" class=\"OWAAutoLink elementToProof\" title=\"https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:32016R0679#art_4\" style=\"margin: 0px; text-align: left;\">Article\n 4(2)</a>)</div>\n</li><li style=\"font-family: Aptos, Aptos_EmbeddedFont, Aptos_MSFontService, Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); list-style-type: &quot;- &quot;;\">\n<div class=\"elementToProof\" style=\"margin: 0px;\">Majority of eKool users are <b>children</b>, which entails\n<b>higher risks </b>(<a href=\"https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:32016R0679#rct_75\" id=\"OWA45335b5e-3d10-b794-0de9-71f6877a37a2\" class=\"OWAAutoLink\" style=\"margin: 0px;\">Recital 75</a>).</div>\n</li><li style=\"font-family: Aptos, Aptos_EmbeddedFont, Aptos_MSFontService, Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); list-style-type: &quot;- &quot;;\">\n<div class=\"elementToProof\">The <b>legal basis</b>&nbsp;for processing can only be (from\n<a href=\"https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:32016R0679#art_6\" id=\"OWAc20a3c02-39d6-2828-7a42-272bb3548e00\" class=\"OWAAutoLink\">\nArticle 6(1)</a><i>):</i></div>\n</li><ul data-editing-info=\"{&quot;applyListStyleFromLevel&quot;:true}\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; list-style-type: circle;\">\n<li style=\"font-family: Aptos, Aptos_EmbeddedFont, Aptos_MSFontService, Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">\n<div class=\"elementToProof\"><b>Consent</b>&nbsp;given by data subject – <i>point (a)</i></div>\n</li><li style=\"font-family: Aptos, Aptos_EmbeddedFont, Aptos_MSFontService, Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">\n<div class=\"elementToProof\">Processing being <b>necessary</b>&nbsp;for:</div>\n</li><ul data-editing-info=\"{&quot;applyListStyleFromLevel&quot;:true}\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;\">\n<li style=\"font-family: Aptos, Aptos_EmbeddedFont, Aptos_MSFontService, Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); list-style-type: &quot;∎ &quot;;\">\n<div class=\"elementToProof\"><b>fulfilling a contract </b>to which data subject is a party to –\n<i>point (b)</i></div>\n</li><li style=\"font-family: Aptos, Aptos_EmbeddedFont, Aptos_MSFontService, Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); list-style-type: &quot;∎ &quot;;\">\n<div class=\"elementToProof\">compliance with a <b>legal obligation</b>&nbsp;–<i>&nbsp;point (c)</i></div>\n</li><li style=\"font-family: Aptos, Aptos_EmbeddedFont, Aptos_MSFontService, Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); list-style-type: &quot;∎ &quot;;\">\n<div class=\"elementToProof\">protecting<b>&nbsp;vital&nbsp;interests </b>of data subject –<i>&nbsp;point (d)</i></div>\n</li><li style=\"font-family: Aptos, Aptos_EmbeddedFont, Aptos_MSFontService, Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); list-style-type: &quot;∎ &quot;;\">\n<div class=\"elementToProof\"><b>public interest</b>&nbsp;–<i>&nbsp;point (e)</i></div>\n</li><li style=\"font-family: Aptos, Aptos_EmbeddedFont, Aptos_MSFontService, Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); list-style-type: &quot;∎ &quot;;\">\n<div class=\"elementToProof\">purposes of <b>legitimate interests</b>&nbsp;by eKool –<i>&nbsp;point (f)</i></div>\n</li></ul>\n</ul>\n<li style=\"font-family: Aptos, Aptos_EmbeddedFont, Aptos_MSFontService, Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); list-style-type: &quot;- &quot;;\">\n<div class=\"elementToProof\" style=\"margin: 0px;\">Going by given consent means it must be \"<b>freely given</b>,\n<b>specific</b>, <b>informed</b>&nbsp;and <b>unambiguous</b>\" (<a href=\"https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:32016R0679#art_4\" id=\"OWAe011611c-cf7a-54aa-06c8-0ed8ede79764\" class=\"OWAAutoLink\" style=\"margin: 0px;\">Article 4(11)</a>), and must\n be as <b>easily withdrawable</b>&nbsp;(<a href=\"https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:32016R0679#art_7\" id=\"OWAa5e45487-770c-9e35-75ce-ac515cc037c1\" class=\"OWAAutoLink\" style=\"margin: 0px;\">Article 7(3)</a>).</div>\n</li><li style=\"font-family: Aptos, Aptos_EmbeddedFont, Aptos_MSFontService, Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); list-style-type: &quot;- &quot;;\">\n<div class=\"elementToProof\">Going by public or legitimate interest also gives data subjects\n<b>Right to object</b>&nbsp;(<a href=\"https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:32016R0679#art_21\" id=\"OWA1d1b0157-24de-2cb6-2722-52c219078426\" class=\"OWAAutoLink\">Article 21</a>).</div>\n</li><li style=\"font-family: Aptos, Aptos_EmbeddedFont, Aptos_MSFontService, Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); list-style-type: &quot;- &quot;;\">\n<div class=\"elementToProof\">Processing, which reveals account existence&nbsp;has to be\n<b>explained&nbsp;upfront</b>&nbsp;(<a href=\"https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:32016R0679#art_13\" id=\"OWA8e052b67-0cfc-c3c9-f7ba-320e4665b3b0\" class=\"OWAAutoLink\">Article 13 – Information to be provided where personal data are collected from the\n data subject</a>)</div>\n</li><li style=\"font-family: Aptos, Aptos_EmbeddedFont, Aptos_MSFontService, Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); list-style-type: &quot;- &quot;;\">\n<div class=\"elementToProof\" style=\"margin: 0px;\">The legal basis should<b>&nbsp;</b>also&nbsp;hold for\n<b>non-registered users</b>, as revealing account non-existence is still <b>processing</b>&nbsp;of\n<b>personal data</b>.</div>\n</li></ul>\n<div class=\"elementToProof\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-family: Aptos, Aptos_EmbeddedFont, Aptos_MSFontService, Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">\n<br>\n</div>\n<div class=\"elementToProof\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-family: Aptos, Aptos_EmbeddedFont, Aptos_MSFontService, Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">\nNot revealing account existence can also be <b>in your business/reputational interests</b>. For example, an attacker could enumerate public contact info of institutions against your vulnerable endpoints. This could be used:</div>\n<ul data-editing-info=\"{&quot;applyListStyleFromLevel&quot;:false,&quot;unorderedStyleType&quot;:2}\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;\">\n<li style=\"font-family: Aptos, Aptos_EmbeddedFont, Aptos_MSFontService, Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); list-style-type: &quot;- &quot;;\">\n<div class=\"elementToProof\" style=\"margin: 0px;\">By your competitors to target your customers with a\n<b>tailored sales pitch</b>, possibly highlighting how your weaknesses might be their strengths. Additionally, this would enable them to gain an accurate\n<b>overview of market</b>, possibly gaining unfair advantage. While customer lists are considered trade secrets, proving misuse might be difficult, so it might be easier to mitigate the vulnerability.</div>\n</li><li style=\"font-family: Aptos, Aptos_EmbeddedFont, Aptos_MSFontService, Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); list-style-type: &quot;- &quot;;\">\n<div class=\"elementToProof\" style=\"margin: 0px;\">By an attacker to exploit some other vulnerabilities in/related to your system,\n<b>causing harm</b>&nbsp;to&nbsp;either eKool, ​institutions that are your customers. For example,\n<b>phishing</b>&nbsp;emails could be sent using eKool's templates after validating an email is associated to an eKool account.</div>\n</li></ul>\n<div class=\"elementToProof\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-family: Aptos, Aptos_EmbeddedFont, Aptos_MSFontService, Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">\n<br>\n</div>\n<div class=\"elementToProof\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-family: Aptos, Aptos_EmbeddedFont, Aptos_MSFontService, Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">\nWe are&nbsp;also interested in any other related comments or thoughts you have regarding this topic. We understand you have a better overview of the specifics of your product and would also be very interested to learn about any other functionality where it might\n not be trivial to mitigate account enumeration vulnerability.</div>\n<div class=\"elementToProof\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-family: Aptos, Aptos_EmbeddedFont, Aptos_MSFontService, Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">\n<br>\n</div>\n<div class=\"elementToProof\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-family: Aptos, Aptos_EmbeddedFont, Aptos_MSFontService, Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">\nBest regards,<br>\nGregor Eesmaa<br>\nComputer Science MSc student<br>\nUniversity of Tartu, Institute of Computer Science</div>\n<div class=\"elementToProof\" style=\"font-family: Aptos, Aptos_EmbeddedFont, Aptos_MSFontService, Calibri, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">\n<br>\n</div>\n<div id=\"appendonsend\"></div>\n\n</body>",
